@Entrepreneur features the latest on the #HackThePandemic initiative, created by Mamaroneck High School sophomore Jerry Orans to provide first responders with personal protective equipment (PPE) while treating COVID-19 positive patients. "I started on March 23rd, and since then we've got over a hundred active makers and three global distribution partners," Jerry says. "We have created about 500 shields, 20-plus intubation boxes, 1,000 Ear savers, and have an order in the works for 20,000 reusable face shields." @mamkrobotics #TigerPride @LMStemAlliance

